This article is about a speech given by the First Lady of the United States, Jill Biden, at an event in Washington, D.C. The speech focused on celebrating Italian American heritage and the contributions of Italian Americans to society. Biden talked about her own family's immigration story and the values they brought with them to America. She also discussed the challenges faced by Italian Americans throughout history and the importance of passing on ancestral values to future generations. Biden highlighted the efforts of her husband, President Joe Biden, to support communities and build a brighter future for all Americans. The article concludes with a message of unity and the importance of sharing the country we call home.